                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-37-victim455 t18330905-37-viclabel222"></join> and live at Arlington, the prisoner was my <rs id="t18330905-37-deflabel223" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-37-defend453 t18330905-37-deflabel223"></join>, and when he went out with straw he had to receive the money for it; on the 1st of June, I sent him with a load of straw, which was sold to Mr. Lee, the prisoner returned and told me he had<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183309050031"></xptr>not received the money for it; it was 26s. the load, but the prisoner was to be allowed 5s. for his expenses; he left my house the same night without notice; he was taken in about a month afterwards.</p>
